  Guardrails are in the plan now, as their own section at the top:

  • One surface only — the web app. No extension, no side panel, no native app, no IWA changes this plan. Those need the web app's bones to exist first.
  • No training UI — "add a skill" means equip an already-trained adapter and prove a plan (the flow that already exists). Training/retraining/versioning stays deferred.
  • Phases ship serially — each phase ends deployed with all checks green before the next starts; no phase-2 work riding in phase-1 commits. The verification section is now a per-phase gate instead of one big
    gate at the end.
  • Phase 1 is intentionally shallow — it recomposes existing components. Built-in tripwire: if a Phase 1 task requires inventing a new subsystem, it's mis-scoped and moves to Phase 2/3 or gets deferred.
  • Zero new server endpoints through the whole plan — the footprint check enforces it.

