  What Phase 3 added, on top of the Phase 1/2 work you already saw committed:

  • IncomingItem is now the app's unit of "something arrived for you" (src/lib/sources/feed.ts). It's the mail row's shape promoted with a
    source id, status chip, and tags, plus mappers from emails, GitHub PRs, and GitHub issues. Row verbs (mark read, reply, trash, open on
    GitHub, …) are now data descriptors instead of hard-coded menus.
  • One generic feed surface (src/components/workbench/feed-list.tsx). The GitHub PR and Issues panels dropped their bespoke spine-row
    renderers and now render through it — that's the second-source proof that the abstraction holds. Their stat strips, filters, and
    connect/error states were kept.
  • ThreadRow and PaneBody are parameterized: the mail list passes Gmail's verbs in explicitly, and ThreadRow renders whatever descriptor
    list it's handed, so a future source's rows get menus for free.
  • ReaderPane split: a reusable DetailShell (draggable header, scroll body, footer bar that folds when narrow) now owns the pane frame,
    and Gmail fills the slots — the tag picker/star in the header, the reply/archive/trash/export verbs in a ReaderFooter. A GitHub detail
    pane can reuse the shell as-is.

